rounds.response:
My turn (X). I analyze the board:

Current Board:
```
 X | _ | _ 
---+---+---
 _ | O | _ 
---+---+---
 _ | _ | O
```

Threats: If O plays 4 next move (impossible here), or any diagonal line. No immediate danger; O has 2 marks (4 & 8), neither forming a row yet.

Tempo: Against an opponent who started in the center (which favors them) I should start grabbing corners to build dual threats.

Best corner still open: upper-right (2) gives me early control toward two possible lines: top row (0-1-2 mid) and the diagonal (0-4-8 which is mine+O already, so 2-4-6 diagonal instead) or next side toward vertical threats.

So I take the corner one on the right edge.

[2]
